# 1080p Cuts - Barbershop Website

## About This Project

1080p Cuts is a website I built for a fictional barbershop located in Brooklyn, Pretoria. The shop caters mainly to students and young professionals, offering quality haircuts at affordable prices. The business used to rely entirely on word-of-mouth and walk-in customers, but this website represents their first step into the digital world.

The goal was to create a clean, professional online presence that feels elegant yet accessible — just like the shop itself.

## What I Used

- **HTML5** for the structure of all pages
- **CSS3** with custom variables for styling and responsive design
- **JavaScript** (vanilla) for all the interactive features
- **Google Maps** integration to show the shop's location
- **Leaflet.js** as an alternative map option

## What the Website Does

### Home Page
The home page welcomes visitors with a hero section that explains what 1080p Cuts is all about. It highlights the four main reasons to choose the shop — affordability, cleanliness, customer service, and location — and includes testimonials from happy clients. There's also a section that explains the shop's move from word-of-mouth to building a digital footprint.

### Services Page
This page lists all the services offered, complete with pricing and durations. Visitors can search for specific services or filter them by category (haircuts, grooming, or details). There's also a gallery where users can click on any image to view it full-size in a lightbox, and a small section showing the grooming products available in-store.

### About Page
The about page tells the story of how 1080p Cuts started in 2020 and grew through loyal customers and word-of-mouth. It explains the shop's philosophy and core values, introduces the barber team, and highlights that this is a single, independent location — not a chain.

### Enquiry Page
This page has a contact form where visitors can send general enquiries, ask about bookings, give feedback, or enquire about group bookings, careers, or sponsorships. The form validates all the inputs before submitting, and there's a character counter for the message field. Once submitted, the form shows a response message based on the type of enquiry.

### Bookings / Contact Page
The bookings page includes a form for scheduling appointments. It validates the user's name, email, phone number, service selection, date, and time. There's also a map showing the shop's location and an accordion section for opening hours. When the form is submitted, the user gets a confirmation message with the option to send the booking details via email.

## What Makes This Site Special

- **Mobile-Friendly** — The layout adapts to any screen size, with a hamburger menu for smaller devices.
- **Dynamic Content** — Services, team members, and testimonials are loaded from JavaScript, making the site easier to update.
- **Search and Filter** — Visitors can search through services or filter them by type.
- **Interactive Gallery** — Images can be clicked to view them full-size in a lightbox.
- **Form Validation** — Both forms check the user's input before submitting and show helpful error messages.
- **Responsive Design** — Everything adjusts smoothly whether you're on a phone, tablet, or desktop computer.

## The Pages

| Page | What It's For |
|------|---------------|
| index.html | Homepage with hero, benefits, testimonials, and call-to-action |
| services.html | Service listings with search, filter, and gallery |
| about.html | Shop story, philosophy, values, and barber team |
| enquire.html | Contact form for general and specific enquiries |
| contact.html | Booking form with map and opening hours |

